COMPONENT NAME: LKM Informix to Informix (SAME SERVER)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data between 2 Informix databases inside the same server. - A view is created on the source database; a synonym is created on the target database. - Verify that both the source and target servers are configured with the same database logging mode.
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module should only be used for data loading between 2 Informix databases inside the SAME SERVER. To load data between 2 distinct servers, use the LKM SQL to SQL Knowledge Module instead.
- Make sure that the Data Server checkbox is checked in your Topology for the Informix Technology and specify your Informix database name in the Server field of your Data Server definition. To do that: 1. Edit the "Informix" Technology definition in the Topology 2. Check the Naming Rules -> Using "Data Server" checkbox 3. Used Term : "Server" 4. Apply your changes 5. Edit your Informix Dataserver definiton 6. In the Server field, enter the name of your Informix database name When using com.informix.jdbc.IfxDriver this is database property value in URL, when using weblogic.jdbc.informix.InformixDriver this is databaseName value in URL.
- Journalizing Options are not implemented in this module.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
